description: India's Under-19 team showcased their dominance by defeating England in the first Youth ODI with a six-wicket victory. Vaibhav Suryavanshi, a 14-year-old debutant, stole the show with a rapid 48 off 19 balls. Abhigyan Kundu's anchored innings ensured a comfortable chase, complementing the bowlers' effort in restricting England to 174.
title: 'Tufano ko ... ': Suryavanshi's Bollywood-inspired post after 5 sixes

author: DWAIPAYAN GHOSH, TAMAGHNA BANERJEE, POULAMI ROY
description: A law student in Kolkata was allegedly gang-raped in her college's security room after being lured with the promise of a key union post. Police have arrested three individuals, including a college alumnus and two current students, following the survivor's complaint and medical corroboration.
title: 'He didn’t let me go': Kolkata law student gangraped after rejecting proposal; accused filmed act

author: SUKUMAR MAHATO
description: A woman filed a police complaint against Padma Shri awardee Swami Pradiptanandaji. She alleged repeated rape at Bharat Sevashram Sangha in Murshidabad. The woman claimed she was promised a teaching job. She further stated she was forced to undergo an abortion. BJP leaders are calling it a conspiracy. Trinamool Congress demands a thorough investigation.
title: 'Want to unveil real face': Bengal woman accuses Padma Shri awardee of rape

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Iranian Foreign Minister Araghchi urged Donald Trump to retract his "disrespectful" remarks about Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, emphasizing that such rhetoric hinders potential nuclear deal negotiations. Araghchi's statement follows recent tensions, including Israeli strikes on Iranian nuclear sites and retaliatory missile launches.
title: 'Disrespectful and condemnable': Iran on Trump's Khamenei remarks

author: JOY SENGUPTA
description: Air India passengers are facing significant disruptions due to flight cancellations and schedule changes. Anish Agarwal's family's Toronto-Pune trip was split across multiple days, while a Pune family's Mumbai-Newark flight was abruptly cancelled, leading to re-routing. These issues stem from fleet reductions, causing international travelers to experience delays, extended layovers, and lack of compensation, sparking widespread frustration.
title: Rescheduling chaos: Flyer says family split across 3 flights; 'had to change all plans'

author: MANASH PRATIM GOHAIN
description: IIT-Madras is contemplating establishing a medical college to potentially elevate its global ranking and foster interdisciplinary research, according to Director V Kamakoti. The institution is also planning global research centers in Dubai, Malaysia, and Germany, alongside a sustainability campus in Puducherry, to enhance its international presence and address global challenges.
title: IIT-Madras eyes global top 50 with major expansion plans

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Aamir Khan's 'Sitaare Zameen Par' has achieved box office success, grossing over Rs 94 crore in its first eight days. Khan's decision to release the film exclusively in cinemas, bypassing OTT platforms, appears to have paid off handsomely. The film's strong performance has surpassed Akshay Kumar's 'Kesari Chapter 2', although it now faces competition from new releases.
title: ‘Sitaare Zameen Par’ box office: Film mints over Rs 94 crore

author: TAMAGHNA BANERJEE
description: A 63-year-old Salt Lake resident was swindled out of Rs 66.6 lakh in an online investment scam after connecting with a woman on a dating app. The woman persuaded him to invest, promising high returns, and added him to a Telegram group.
title: Online dating app turns costly: 63-yr-old Bengal man duped of Rs 66.6 lakh

author: TNN
description: A 17-year-old social media content creator was allegedly drugged and sexually assaulted by a video blogger during a shoot at a Gorakhpur club. The incident came to light after the girl's family filed a police complaint. Police have arrested the main accused, a Raptinagar resident, and are investigating the involvement of two others. The survivor is receiving mental health support.
title: UP horror: YouTuber drugged, sexually assaulted by vlogger during shoot

description: During the Rath Yatra in Puri, approximately 750 devotees were hospitalized due to exhaustion and crowd pressure. Health officials reported that over 230 individuals were admitted to the Infectious Disease Hospital, while around 520 received treatment at the district headquarters hospital.

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi will embark on a five-nation tour commencing July 2, including first-ever visits to Ghana, Trinidad and Tobago, and Namibia. He will attend the Brics summit in Brazil, discussing global issues and holding bilateral meetings.

author: REEBA ZACHARIAH AND SAURABH SINHA
description: Tata Group took swift disciplinary action, suspending four senior officials from Air India SATS and warning others, after a video surfaced showing executives partying shortly after the tragic June 12 Air India flight 171 crash. The celebration, held at the Gurugram office on June 20, sparked public outrage, with over 3.
title: Tatas suspend 4 after Air India SATS party video sparks outrage

author: SAGAR KUMAR MUTHA
description: The Telangana High Court overturned the BRS government's 2021 order, which had allocated 3.7 acres of prime land in Hyderabad to the International Arbitration and Mediation Centre (IAMC) free of charge. The court cited violations of land revenue laws and alienation rules, noting undue haste in the allotment to a private entity.
title: Telangana HC cancels land allotment to international arbitration centre in Hyderabad
